        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — constitutive law and contact fidelity",
        "description": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive model for Ti-6Al-4V with published material constants (Boyer 1994); frictional contact (μ=0.23, Coulomb) at screw-rod interface. Model form justified by literature precedent and sensitivity study showing <2% QoI change when switching to multilinear isotropic hardening. Gradation 3: documented model form justification with supporting sensitivity analysis."
      },
      "rationale": "Model form choices (BISO plasticity, frictional contact, rigid fixture representation) are consistent with published FDA guidance and peer-reviewed literature on pedicle screw FEA. A model form sensitivity study varying the contact friction coefficient (μ = 0.15 to 0.35) and plasticity model (BISO vs. MISO) confirmed QoI insensitivity within 2%, supporting Gradation 3."
